Commentary: some swing first up. First signs of swing this series. Pitches on a good length and moves away, Walton guides a cut to backward point

Commentary: quickly picks the length and hammers that away. Back of a length on middle, Walton whips his wrists through the line to get that behind square. Clever execution

Commentary: that's sloppy all around. A very wide short delivery outside off. Walton lets it go, the keeper fumbles. Should have been a wide too.
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, 1 bye

Commentary: that's terrific. A harrying bouncer but it's excellently directed too. A bouncer on middle and leg, Lewis takes his eyes off the ball and avoids it
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, no run

Commentary: back of a length on leg, clipped to backward square leg
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: a slower ball, short and slow, slips down leg
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, 1 wide

Commentary: over short fine leg for four. That's good bowling. Digs this in, short outside off, hustles Walton for pace who pulls but is in no control of it. It skews off the leading edge over fine leg for four
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length down leg, nudged to short fine leg for a single
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: lovely line. Good length around off, impeccable. All Walton can do is block
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Walton, no run

Commentary: just slightly short. Not a bad ball. But Walton likes the pull, hammers it away past midwicket for a couple
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Walton, 2 runs

Commentary: picks the length early again and then swats the medium pace (at best) past midwicket. Cannot drop short with that pace
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Walton, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and straight from Karim, pushed to mid-on for a quick run. That's good. Dots only build pressure
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: good finish. Fuller than a good length around off, thick inside edge into the pad.
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Lewis, no run

Commentary: drifts down leg again for a wide
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, 1 wide

Commentary: fullish line outside off, a thick inside edge past the stumps to short fine leg.
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, no run

Commentary: that's tripe. Digs it in down leg, sits up for Walton to just swivel-pull past short fine leg for four. He'll take that
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, FOUR runs

Commentary: well bowled. Full and straight, defended towards mid-on
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, no run

Commentary: that isn't good bowling. He hasn't learnt, but gets away with this. Short again outside off, pulled merrily to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: a slower delivery outside off, overpitched half-volley. Lewis accepts the gift with a caress through the covers for four
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, FOUR runs

Commentary: good end. Tight, around off, defended towards cover for a single.
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: short down leg, Lewis tries to help that for six over fine leg, but gets only some bat on it. The keeper dives forward to his right but can't get there
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Lewis, no run

Commentary: flat down leg, worked to square leg
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: flat on middle, pushed down to long-on. No turn yet
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: worked to wide mid-on for a single
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: lovely clean swing. Tossed that up outside off, overpitched and Walton got underneath that. Way over long-off. Why keep it down when you have this repertoire?
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Walton, SIX runs

Commentary: flat on middle, pushed to long-on for a single
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: flat and straight, driven to long-on. Nice batting from Walton, thinking cricket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: should have been a run-out. Flat and quick down leg, off the pad towards square leg. Walton calls Lewis through, but he is quick to take off. A bad throws enables Lewis to get back in time. The worst part is yet to come, Shenwari and Lewis, with his momentum, collide.

Commentary: and a wicket right after the stoppage. It's full and straight, right in Walton's wheelhouse. Walton is able to get underneath that but isn't able to get much behind it. A mis-timed skew more than anything carries to long-on. Walton done in by the injury to his team-mate. Sucked away his momentum

Dismissal_text: CAK Walton c Noor Ali Zadran b Mohammad Nabi 29 (17b 4x4 1x6) SR: 170.58

Commentary: Lewis doesn't care about momentum or his shoulder. Flat outside off, Lewis runs down and lays into a lofted drive which goes out of Warner Park. Clean ball-striking
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, SIX runs

Commentary: good stop. Short on middle and leg, Lewis swivels into a sweep. Short fine leg dives to his right to save three
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: Samuels carries on from his form last evening. Short and wide outside off, caressed through cover for a couple.

Commentary: flat down leg, Lewis misses a sweep and is struck on the pad. Pitched well outside leg
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Lewis, no run

Commentary: full and straight, quick. Lewis wants to hit this over midwicket but it's too full. Improvises a checked flick to long-on
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: too full. Overpitched, straight. Shovelled to midwicket. No turn so it takes the inside half of the bat
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Samuels, no run

Commentary: better length. Quick and straight, Samuels presses forward to defend
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Samuels, no run

Commentary: darted in down leg, off the pad towards point. Still no turn
Commentary_short: Amir Hamza to Samuels, no run

Commentary: excellent finish from Hamza. Flat on off and middle, Samuels shimmies down but the length isn't there for an attacking shot, so he defends. Just one off the over.

Commentary: full and straight, pushed to long-off for one
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: plenty of sixes tonight. Nabi pitches a full delivery from around the wicket. the idea is to cramp him for room but with Samuels' open stance, it's an invitation and he accepts. Slugged over midwicket

Commentary: pushed to long-off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Samuels, 1 run

Commentary: fired in on middle, extremely quick. Defended back
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, no run

Commentary: strays down leg, nudged towards square leg for a couple. Nicely played, knew what he wanted and execution good too
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, 2 runs

Commentary: another dart down leg, clipped to long-on for one
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, hit away to the sweeper cover

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Samuels swings too hard at that and misses. No footwork.

Commentary: on the pads, clipped to deep midwicket

Commentary: nice lines. Around off on a length, pushed towards cover
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Lewis, no run

Commentary: better. A yorker outside off, no bat on that from Lewis
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Lewis, no run

Commentary: flat and straight, driven back to the bowler from the back foot. Bang on target. The perfect line for a legspinner

Commentary: quicker, fuller, the line the same. Hit back again

Commentary: goes through the keeper's legs. Flat down leg, goes past Lewis' sweep. The keeper is blinded but concedes two. Goes down as a drop. Was there glove?

Commentary: flat outside off, pushed to cover. Playing him off the back foot
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Lewis, no run

Commentary: quick down leg, nudged to deep midwicket. Still off the back foot. Gives him a fraction of a second more
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: Samuels doesn't read him either. Quick on leg, looking to read him off the pitch, but is undone by Rashid's quicker pace and flatter trajectory. Hit on the pad
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Samuels, no run

Commentary: and again. Lewis falls in the same fashion again and again and again and again. A short delivery on middle and leg, Lewis picks the length early and looks to clear midwicket but doesn't get enough on it. Straight to deep midwicket who takes a simple reverse-cupped catch on the boundary. Two in two this series, and a countless number of times prior too, the method of dismissal is the same

Dismissal_text: E Lewis c Gulbadin Naib b Karim Janat 25 (28b 1x4 1x6) SR: 89.28

Commentary: full and straight, a thick inside edge towards square leg
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: a nice yorker on leg, jammed out. Samuels opening up his stance
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Samuels, no run

Commentary: fullish on leg stump, a mis-timed heave finds long-on
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Samuels, 1 run

Commentary: full and straight again, clipped to midwicket
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: well bowled, a slower ball outside off. Samuels' heave results in a checked drive towards cover

Commentary: fires it at a length, flat on off stump, Samuels pokes it into the of side off the back foot but has too much bat to steal a single

Commentary: googly, tossed up at length outside off stump, goes forwards drops it into the off side tentatively. He didn't pick that
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Samuels, no run

Commentary: on the back foot now, watches this length ball carefully and defends it off the back foot under his eyes
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Samuels, no run

Commentary: good length, off stump, defended back down the pitch
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Samuels, no run

Commentary: good length at middle stump, goes deep in the crease and tickles this through vacant square leg
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Samuels, 1 run

Commentary: good length, quick at off stump, forward defence
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Simmons, no run

Commentary: overpitched and angled in at leg stump. Samuels looks to make room but he's cramped, can only bunt it back down the pitch

Commentary: full, into the pads, harried flick, straight to deep square leg

Commentary: outfoxes him again with a slower ball. This is of a similar line and length, draws him forward and forces him to defend at middle stump

Commentary: misses the yorker marginally, but Simmons can only drill this low full toss to long-on off his pads

Commentary: shot. A great over gets relegated to just-about-good. Samuels walks towards the leg side to make room, and he gets a nice overpitched ball at middle stump. Brings the bat down nicely and finishes a beautiful swing to lift this straight over his partner and to long-off's left

Commentary: a googly first up, back of a length and spinning inside from outside off. Steps out and cramps himself, tickles it to short fine leg's left

Commentary: back of a length, off stump, Samuels gets behind the line and punches off the back foot to find sweeper cover

Commentary: a slider pushed back of a length, steps out again but there's rarely any room from Rashid. Simmons tucks this towards deep midwicket who runs in quickly and keeps it to one

Commentary: googly, back of a length at off stump, chopped to backward point

Commentary: he stays in the crease this time. Rashid fires this back of a length, probably expecting him to be down the track. But he has converted it into a long-hop by going deep. Commentary: makes a lot of room, very early. Rashid drops it wide outside off to counter, but he shimmies quickly and recovers to get the square cut. Sweeper runs to his left to clean up

Commentary: full and aimed for middle stump. Samuels is on the move, but the angle cramps him. He jams it back to the bowler

Commentary: this is sensational death bowling. In the blockhole, just outside off stump. There's room for Samuels, but he cannot get bat onto his attempted slice. Beaten,

Commentary: holes out. A length ball on leg stump, enough room, and right in the slot. But he doesn't get under this slog. Gets it off the inside half of the bat and lobs it up gently for long-on who grabs it in front of his throat

Commentary: what a spell. Sees Simmons go down leg side, adjusts to throw this wide of him. It's a length ball in the end, but it's enough of a change up to disturb the batsman's plans. He steps out and swings away from his body, and is beaten on the under edge
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Simmons, no run

Commentary: ooohhhh misses out. Length ball, nice and juicy outside off stump. No feet from him as he looks to bludgeon this on the up. But he toe-ends it and the bowler gets across to field it

Commentary: doesn't miss this! Knee-height full toss, just outside off stump. Brathwaite already has his front leg out of the way in his stance. Just stands tall and sways this away, flat and powerfully, wide of long-on. Like a cricket elitist dismissing T20s

Commentary: slower length ball outside off stump, can't time this slog well enough. It's along the floor and straight to long-on

Commentary: falls in front of deep square leg. A bouncer that he drags from outside off stump with a top edge. Hands seductively in front of Noor Ali at deep square. He takes the bait and dives forward but it drops short of him. Recovers with some pain on his shoulder and fires a shocking throw halfway down the pitch that Shafiqullah can't get to with a Supermanesque dive. Overthrows.

Commentary: superb. Drifts a back-of-the-hand slower ball in outside off, at a yorker length, and beats the batsman's swipe

Commentary: length ball at middle stump, backs away and clubs this on the up, but it's along the floor and slightly to long-on's right

Commentary: on the pads to start, Naib misses a flick and is struck on the pad.

Commentary: flat outside off, keeps low, goes underneath Naib's bat. Typical Badree start

Commentary: flat and straight, Naib doesn't mind getting forward to defend

Commentary: quick. Flat on off, hurries Naib for pace, who badly miscues a pull to cover

Commentary: this is pushed through again. Flat and quick outside off, punched to mid-off for a single. Too many dots already in this over

Commentary: just out of reach of brathwaite, running back from mid-on. Fullish outside off, another badly-timed pull makes its way towards long-off. Narine lets Brathwaite try. Just a hand on that from Brathwaite

Commentary: a wild swing. Full and wide from around the wicket, just inside the tramline but Naib misses

Commentary: that's far too wide. Full delivery but too wide outside off, it's called.

Commentary: a low full toss outside off, punched wide of cover for a couple. Long-off cleans up. Two more

Commentary: good end, breaks the unpredictability by executing a straight yorker. Chipped to mid-on

Commentary: overpitched on leg, skewed to long-on for a run

Commentary: excellent bowling. Sees Noor Ali coming so fires this down leg. Noor Ali gets pad on it somehow

Commentary: fullish outside off, a wild mow over cover results in a thick inside edge past the stumps for a run

Commentary: quick, accurate, straight, Punched to mid-off
Commentary_short: Badree to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: there is the first boundary of the innings. Shortish delivery outside off, Gulbadin gets hold of this and sends it way over long-on. Just what Afghanistan need
Commentary_short: Badree to Gulbadin Naib, SIX runs

Commentary: and comes back with the wicket. Great bowling. Quick and straight, on leg. Gulbadin plays around the ball, gets there late and doesn't make contact. All requisites for a wicket against Badree.

Commentary: much better from Noor Ali. Good choice of stroke. Back of a length on middle and leg, sits up for Noor Ali to spank over point. No one there.

Commentary: another one falls. A hard length. Boundary and wicket. Afghanistan handicapping themselves. Back of a length on leg, Noor Ali is far too late on his pull and the ball lobs to short fine leg. A simple catch. Afghanistan batsmen look so hurried for pace, not just tonight but yesterday too. A sign of the step-up in quality they are facing

Commentary: two in two. Afghanistan falling away. Back of a length on off, Samiullah tries to get one to third man but the ball bounces extra and takes a thin edge through to the keeper. Beaten in pace and bounce again. Not looking too good

Commentary: good length outside off, dabbed towards point.

Commentary: just short of Taylor at short fine leg. Good length on middle, Nabi gets across his stumps and clips the ball in the air towards short fine leg, where Taylor dives forward but the ball lands in front.

Commentary: flat outside off, pushed back to the bowler

Commentary: slow, full delivery on middle is pushed to long-on

Commentary: flat, straight, spinning back in, pushed towards cover. Struggling to hit gaps

Commentary: drifts down leg, off the pad towards short fine leg

Commentary: on a length on off, clipped to square leg

Commentary: shortish delivery outside off, played to Kesrick again at cover. Early no this time

Commentary: good length outside off, carved down to third man

Commentary: full and straight, played back
